		<TR><TD ALIGN="CENTER" colspan="3">
		
		<h3><FONT FACE="ARIAL,HELVETICA">CIRCUS PERFORMERS FORMERLY OF CIRQUE DU SOLEIL HEADLINE </font></H3>
		</TD></TR>
		<TR><TD>&nbsp;</td></tr>
		<TR><TD colspan="3">
		<FONT FACE="ARIAL,HELVETICA" SIZE="2"><P>
<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="LINE-HEIGHT: normal; TEXT-INDENT: 0in"><SPAN><FONT size=2><FONT face=Arial>ROSEVILLE &#8211; Galleria at Roseville will celebrate its grand opening with three days of events beginning on Friday, August 25, 2000 and headlined by world-renowned performers formerly of Cirque du Soleil.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN>Internationally known for their amazing acrobatic and gymnastic feats, four incredible acts will be featured including special aerial performances.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Galleria at Roseville&#8217;s grand opening entertainment also includes a host of other talented performers and activities, which will culminate with a fireworks extravaganza at 9:00 p.m. on August 25.<?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" /><o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="LINE-HEIGHT: normal; TEXT-INDENT: 0in"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><FONT face=Arial>The circus performances and the fireworks display are just a few of the family-friendly activities planned to celebrate the opening of the 1.1 million square foot regional shopping center.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Galleria at Roseville will open its doors on August 25 at 10:00 a.m. following the unveiling of The Kids Gallery &#8211; a wall of more than 2,300 hand-painted tiles benefiting the United Way and Roseville Arts Center &#8211; and an official shopping center unveiling ceremony.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Both events are open to the public. <o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="LINE-HEIGHT: normal; TEXT-INDENT: 0in"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><FONT face=Arial>Highlighting the weekend&#8217;s grand opening activities will be appearances by professional basketball players Jon Barry and Scott Pollard, who will sign autographs on Sunday August 27 from 2:00 p.m. to 4:00 p.m. (Limit one autograph per person).<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Throughout the weekend, the Galleria has scheduled a variety of entertainment including Disney characters, fashion events and musical performances from Jellyeye, a unique theatrical performance of dance and drum.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>A special feature of the grand opening festivities will include register-to-win prizes, such as a $3,000 &#8220;shopping spree&#8221; given away each day August 25 through 27 and a brand new car valued at $15,000, courtesy of the Roseville Automall, awarded on September 5.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN>Register-to-win at the Galleria and the Roseville Automall and get complete rules and regulations.<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Arial>Located in South Placer County at Galleria Boulevard and Roseville Parkway off Highway 65 and Interstate 80, the shopping center will feature more then 120 retailers anchored by Nordstrom, Macy&#8217;s, JCPenney and Sears and includes new-to-market specialty merchants including Crate &amp; Barrel (opening Spring 2001), J.Jill and Restoration Hardware.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Unique to the Sacramento region, the Galleria will also feature The Promenade &#8211; an outdoor pedestrian streetscape including upscale restaurants and distinctive retailers.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>The Promenade is designed as an urban village with street-side cafes, a dramatic water feature, children&#8217;s play area and a fireplace.</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>
<P><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Arial>Galleria at Roseville is owned and developed by Chicago-based Urban Shopping Centers, Inc. (NYSE: URB), a self-administered real estate investment trust (REIT), which is in the business of owning, acquiring, managing, leasing, developing and redeveloping super-regional and regional malls. The company opened Brandon TownCenter in Tampa, Florida in February 1995, Wolfchase Galleria in Memphis, Tennessee in February 1997, a second Tampa-area mall, Citrus Park Town Center, in March 1999, and expects to open Galleria at Roseville on August 25, 2000 and The Streets at Southpoint in Durham, North Carolina in spring 2002. Urban Shopping Centers, Inc. owns interests in several of the premier shopping centers in the United States including Oakbrook Center (Oak Brook, Illinois), Century City Shopping Center &amp; Marketplace (Los Angeles, California), Water Tower Place (Chicago, Illinois), Old Orchard Center (Skokie, Illinois), Copley Place (Boston, Massachusetts),San Francisco Shopping Centre (San Francisco, California), and The Galleria (Houston, Texas), as well as in Urban Retail Properties Co., its property management, leasing and development affiliate. Urban Retail Properties Co. is one of the nation's largest retail property managers, managing more than 59 million square feet of space in 26 states and the District of Columbia.</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Arial>For more information on Galleria at Roseville or to schedule an on-site interview, please contact Mitch Zak at (916) 446-6667.</FONT></SPAN></P>
		<p>&nbsp;</p>
		 
